			  	actually what i wanted to do was get rid of fleets entirely. <br />
give the players the ability to send a bunch of dooms, some frigates, support ships, carriers and organize them with the applet like a modern battlegroup.<br />
damage would then occur in rings rather than the one on one (which is completely unrealistic) in AS. it could also lead to better tactics (i.e. if the captain of a destroyer was experienced decided to hit the opposing forces doom and managed to get thru the support ring, the doom would take critical damage just like if a modern exocet managed to penetrate the aegis shield of a modern carrier battle group and got past the last ditch phalanx CIWS/RAM systems..roughly equivalent to shields in AS). this tactical screening is not currently present in AS which makes AS's system unrealistic.<br />
giving each ship an experience rather than an entire fleet makes the system much better to play. also you cant have 2 million ship vs 2 million ship wars in AS which isnt much fun. the 20 fleet limit is kinda lame.<br />
