				posted 2005-01-17 17:38&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;
				<A href="edit.php?board=player&id=15416"><IMG alt="Edit/Delete Message" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/edit.gif" border=0></A> 
			    <A href="reply.php?board=player&id=15248"><IMG alt="Reply w/Quote" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/quote.gif" border=0></A>
			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	AM is different in AS in many ways...<br />
<br />
if we are talking about the maritel version of AM:<br />
AM was done in C, instead of C++, this has major implications since AS revolves around classes, inheritance, and abstract classes (im not a big fan of abstract classes :( )<br />
<br />
The redone version i believe is done in php, i don't think i need to go any further on that.<br />
<br />
Fluffy, i would not recommend doing a web based game in C/asm unless you can do the following:<br />
raid Starbucks for free coffee<br />
compile C code in your head<br />
do without social contact for 6 months<br />
<br />
if you meet the above requirements, go right ahead.<br />
I am all for performance... but there comes a point when it just isn't worth it from the developer's perspective. There is a crap load of stuff that goes behind the scenes of AS:<br />
garbage clean up (we try not to rely on that peice of korean code :/)<br />
database synchronization (possible pitfalls if u don't plan it out properly)<br />
inter-relational objects ( major pitfalls. Some AS bugs happen this way)<br />
page processor with page table (AS has its own implemented system, a bit limitting but gets the job done)<br />
apache-AS module (i mean, do u really want to compile all of the game as an apache module? if you do, i can no longer take you seriously)<br />
scripting system (you need a way to load &quot;game data&quot; ie projects)<br />
<br />
well you get the idea, its no walk in the park. I strongly discourage coding it in plain C. Take this from a guy who has nightmares about syntax errors, and other code related junk. (the doctor says ill be fine as long as i take my meds :-P )<br />
<br />
Seiffer, the code is inflexible... you never had to add a major element to the game before. This is mainly because AS doesn't have a real system for inter-relational objects, it simply relies on the program not to forget anything.<p><br>&lt;zbyte645795&gt;	so tita, there is two of me!<br />
&lt;zbyte645795&gt;	one to pimp out<br />
&lt;zbyte64&gt;	the other to keep to urself<br />
&lt;TitaniaX&gt;	or i could just pimp both of you and get twice as much			   <P align=right></P>
