			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	if AS was done in php, you would see a major performance decrease. AS caches all of AS into memory and generates lots of variables and lists from the database upon start up. To have all these variables either computed on the fly or stored in the database would be rather inefficient. The DB caching system is a very good idea in the instance of AS. AS is definately more complex then other games in that there are lots of related variables. It also helps to hide all the sql syntax and just access everything as you would an object.<br />
<br />
Lemme just recap:<br />
The reason AS was done in C++ is because of performance. PHP is good for simpler games/projects - AS is not a simple game.<br />
<br />
